Janki  is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Gołdap, within Gołdap County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, which is close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  south-west of Gołdap and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
